title: Sonny Rollins - The quartets [EAC FLAC]
description:
This LP contains the six songs originally on The Bridge (his comeback album after three years of retirement) plus seven additional items from 1962 and 1964 that co-star guitarist Jim Hall. At first when Rollins reappeared his style was virtually unchanged from 1959 but gradually it loosened up and became freer. This attractive two-fer, which is highlighted by "Without a Song," "Don't Stop the Carnival" and "If Ever I Would Leave You," has important music that is essential for all Sonny Rollins collectors.


Track Listing

1- God Bless the Child (Billie Holiday / Arthur Herzog, Jr.)

2- John S. (Sonny Rollins)

3- You Do Something to Me (Cole Porter)

4- Where Are You? (Harold Adamson / Jimmy McHugh)

5- Without a Song (Edward Eliscu / Billy Rose / Vincent Youmans)

6- The Bridge (Sonny Rollins)

7- If Ever I Would Leave You (Alan Jay Lerner / Frederick Loewe)

8- The Night Has a Thousand Eyes (Buddy Bernier / Jerry Brainin)
